  "text": "The changes in the signal amplitude are more precisely seen in the difference spectra (compare figure 4(a) ) relative to T = 0 fs. For DS α a weaker decrease of signal amplitude compared to DS β can be observed, which confirms the different dynamics already seen in transient absorption and the higher stability of |α . Comparing the difference spectra for T = 50 and 250 fs, a progressive decrease to lower wavenumbers of the combined SE and GSB signal can be observed. At T = 0 the signal consists of GSB and SE contributions. After a given population time (T = 50 fs) the signal shifts to lower wavenumbers as the SE contribution is influenced by a Stokes shift. As the lifetime in the Soret band is ≈ 150 fs [CITATION_1] the Stokes-shifted SE vanishes for T 150 fs while the GSB is still maintained, leading to the observed stronger signal decrease at lower wavenumbers. The most important additional feature is an increasing signal amplitude for DS β at wavenumbers corresponding to the lower energetic state |α , which is a consequence of a coupling between |β and |α . This signal is indicative of relaxation from |β into |α since molecules excited into |β now show absorption at frequencies corresponding to the state |α while at the same time the SE signal for |β decreases.",
